      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <!-- Why Finance Professionals -->
      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Why This Matters for Finance Professionals</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">點解金融從業者要關注</span>
      </h2>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">Prediction market prices function as a <span class="text-white">real-time probability feed</span>. Market-implied probabilities for Fed rate decisions, geopolitical outcomes, and policy changes update faster and more accurately than traditional research reports. If your book is long rates, you can buy "Fed holds rates" contracts as a hedge — the binary payoff structure makes risk/reward simple to calculate.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">預測市場價格充當<span class="text-white">實時概率feed</span>。Fed利率決定、地緣政治結果和政策變動嘅market implied probabilities比傳統研究報告更新更快、更準確。如果你嘅倉位做多利率，你可以買「Fed維持利率」合約作為對沖 — binary payoff結構令風險/回報計算簡單。</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        <span class="lang-en">ICE — parent company of NYSE — investing ~$2 billion signals unambiguously: traditional exchange operators see prediction markets as a next-generation information market. When the NYSE's parent company commits this level of capital, the institutional legitimacy question is settled.</span>
        <span class="lang-zh">ICE — NYSE嘅母公司 — 投資~$20億嘅信號毫不含糊：傳統交易所運營商認為預測市場係下一代信息市場。當NYSE母公司投入呢個級別嘅資金，機構合法性嘅問題已經解決。</span>
      </p>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <!-- Risks -->
      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-16 mb-6">
        <span class="lang-en">Risks</span><span class="lang-zh">風險</span>
      </h2>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3">
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Not regulated by SFC</span> — no deposit protection, no investor recourse in Hong Kong</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">唔受SFC監管</span> — 香港冇存款保障，冇投資者追索權</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Resolution disputes</span> — UMA oracle can take 4-6 days to resolve disputed markets. During this time, your capital is locked</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">Resolution爭議</span> — UMA oracle可能需要4-6日resolve有爭議嘅markets。期間你嘅資金被鎖定</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Thin liquidity on niche markets</span> — large positions in low-volume markets will face significant slippage</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">冷門市場流動性薄</span> — 低成交量market嘅大額倉位會有顯著滑點</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Smart contract risk</span> — settlement on Polygon via CTF contracts. No major incidents to date, but risk is non-zero</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">智能合約風險</span> — 通過Polygon上嘅CTF contracts結算。至今冇重大事故，但風險唔係零</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Volume double-counting</span> — Paradigm research (Dec 2025) showed most analytics dashboards double-count Polymarket volume due to on-chain data complexity. Reported figures may be inflated</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">交易量重複計算</span> — Paradigm研究（2025年12月）顯示大部分分析dashboard因鏈上數據複雜性而重複計算Polymarket交易量。報告數字可能被誇大</span></li>
        <li><span class="lang-en"><span class="text-white">Hybrid architecture trust assumption</span> — order matching is centralized. You trust the operator to match fairly. Settlement is on-chain, but execution quality depends on the off-chain matching engine</span><span class="lang-zh"><span class="text-white">混合架構信任假設</span> — order matching係中心化嘅。你信任operator公平matching。Settlement係on-chain，但execution quality取決於off-chain matching engine</span></li>
      </ul>

